WEBVTT

00:00:00.801 --> 00:00:03.871 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:38%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:13.607 --> 00:01:15.275 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:25%
[CHANTING]

00:01:24.284 --> 00:01:27.888 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
[NARRATOR] Samadhi is an 
ancient Sanskrit word for which

00:01:27.888 --> 00:01:29.556 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:45%
there's no
modern equivalent.

00:01:32.893 --> 00:01:35.195 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:53%
There's a fundamental
challenge with making

00:01:35.195 --> 00:01:37.130 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:53%
a film about Samadhi.

00:01:38.498 --> 00:01:40.968 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
Samadhi points to
something that can't be

00:01:40.968 --> 00:01:43.270 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:75%
conveyed on the level of mind.

00:01:54.348 --> 00:01:57.584 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
This film is simply
the outer manifestation

00:01:57.584 --> 00:01:59.553 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:61%
of my own inner journey.

00:02:00.487 --> 00:02:03.957 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
The intention is not to
teach you about Samadhi

00:02:03.957 --> 00:02:06.994 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:56%
or provide information
for your mind,

00:02:06.994 --> 00:02:10.998 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:75%
but to inspire you to directly
discover your true nature.

00:02:24.077 --> 00:02:26.747 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:48%
Samadhi is relevant
now more than ever.

00:02:29.383 --> 00:02:32.285 align:middle line:79% position:38% size:68%
We are at a time in history
where we have not only

00:02:32.285 --> 00:02:36.690 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
forgotten Samadhi, but we've
forgotten what we forgot.

00:02:43.897 --> 00:02:49.636 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
This forgetting is Maya,
the illusion of the self.

00:03:14.261 --> 00:03:16.763 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:38%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:03:28.308 --> 00:03:33.213 align:middle line:79% position:38% size:68%
As humans, most of us live
immersed in our daily lives

00:03:33.213 --> 00:03:36.783 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:65%
with little thought of who
we are, why we are here,

00:03:36.783 --> 00:03:37.784 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:53%
or where we're going.

00:03:42.456 --> 00:03:48.261 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:75%
Most of us have never realized
the true self, the soul,

00:03:48.261 --> 00:03:51.765 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
or what the Buddha
called anata, that which

00:03:51.765 --> 00:03:54.668 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:61%
is beyond name and form.

00:03:54.668 --> 00:03:55.735 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:41%
Beyond thinking.

00:03:57.170 --> 00:04:01.641 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:65%
As a result, we believe we
are these limited bodies.

00:04:04.611 --> 00:04:08.849 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
We live in fear, either
conscious or unconscious,

00:04:08.849 --> 00:04:12.986 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
that the limited self structure
that we are identified with

00:04:12.986 --> 00:04:14.187 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:23%
will die.

00:04:25.866 --> 00:04:28.201 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:43%
In today's world,
the vast majority

00:04:28.201 --> 00:04:31.271 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
of people who are engaged
in religious or spiritual

00:04:31.271 --> 00:04:37.177 align:middle line:79% position:36% size:73%
practices, such as yoga,
prayer, meditation, chanting,

00:04:37.177 --> 00:04:41.081 align:middle line:79% position:38% size:68%
or any kind of ritual, or
practicing techniques which

00:04:41.081 --> 00:04:44.017 align:middle line:79% position:38% size:68%
are conditioned which means
they are just part

00:04:44.017 --> 00:04:45.652 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:53%
of the ego construct.

00:04:49.756 --> 00:04:53.560 align:middle line:79% position:38% size:68%
The seeking and the
activity isn't the problem.

00:04:53.560 --> 00:04:57.397 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
Thinking you have found the
answer in some external form

00:04:57.397 --> 00:04:58.198 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:38%
is the problem.

00:05:01.101 --> 00:05:04.738 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:50%
Spirituality, in its
most common form,

00:05:04.738 --> 00:05:07.474 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
is no different than the
pathological thinking

00:05:07.474 --> 00:05:09.075 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:70%
that is going on everywhere.

00:05:10.944 --> 00:05:14.147 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:56%
It is a further
agitation of the mind.

00:05:14.147 --> 00:05:18.151 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
More human doing as
opposed to human being.

00:05:19.719 --> 00:05:24.691 align:middle line:79% position:36% size:73%
The ego construct wants more
money, more power, more love,

00:05:24.691 --> 00:05:26.126 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:48%
more of everything.

00:05:28.962 --> 00:05:31.331 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:56%
Those on the so-called
spiritual path

00:05:31.331 --> 00:05:37.938 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
desire to be more spiritual,
more awake, more equanimous,

00:05:37.938 --> 00:05:41.575 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:81%
more peaceful, more enlightened.

00:05:43.410 --> 00:05:46.813 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:45%
The danger for you
watching this film

00:05:46.813 --> 00:05:50.483 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
is that your mind will
want to acquire Samadhi.

00:05:53.220 --> 00:05:55.855 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:56%
Even more dangerous is
that your mind might

00:05:55.855 --> 00:05:58.191 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:75%
think it has acquired Samadhi.

00:06:01.328 --> 00:06:04.197 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
Whenever there's a desire
to attain something,

00:06:04.197 --> 00:06:07.334 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
you can be sure it's the
ego construct at work.

00:06:08.635 --> 00:06:11.438 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:50%
Samadhi is not about
attaining or adding

00:06:11.438 --> 00:06:13.240 align:middle line:85% position:46% size:68%
something more to yourself.

00:06:18.078 --> 00:06:23.016 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
To realize Samadhi is to
learn to die before you die.

00:06:26.920 --> 00:06:32.092 align:start line:79% position:44% size:78%
Life and death are like yin and
yang, an inseparable continuum

00:06:32.092 --> 00:06:36.229 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
endlessly unfolding with
no beginning and no end.

00:06:37.597 --> 00:06:41.601 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
When we push away death,
we also push away life.

00:06:42.836 --> 00:06:47.007 align:middle line:79% position:36% size:73%
When you experience the truth
directly of who you are,

00:06:47.007 --> 00:06:49.909 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:56%
there is no longer any
fear of life or death.

00:06:54.648 --> 00:06:58.151 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
We are told who we are by
our society and our culture.

00:06:59.319 --> 00:07:01.888 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
And at the same time, we
are slaves to the deeper

00:07:01.888 --> 00:07:05.091 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:56%
unconscious biological
craving and aversion

00:07:05.091 --> 00:07:06.693 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:63%
that governs our choices.

00:07:12.966 --> 00:07:15.835 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
The ego construct is nothing
more than the impulse

00:07:15.835 --> 00:07:16.636 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:25%
to repeat.

00:07:17.704 --> 00:07:20.974 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:56%
It's simply the path
that energy once took,

00:07:20.974 --> 00:07:24.544 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
and the tendency for the
energy to take that path again,

00:07:24.544 --> 00:07:27.447 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:65%
whether it is positive or
negative for the organism.

00:07:33.486 --> 00:07:36.756 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
There are endless levels
of memory or mind,

00:07:36.756 --> 00:07:39.025 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:58%
spirals within spirals.

00:07:39.959 --> 00:07:43.263 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
When your consciousness
identifies with this mind

00:07:43.263 --> 00:07:47.534 align:middle line:79% position:36% size:73%
or ego construct, it ties you
to social conditioning,

00:07:47.534 --> 00:07:50.170 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:81%
which you could call the matrix.

00:07:54.941 --> 00:07:58.278 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
There are aspects of the ego
that we can be conscious of,

00:07:58.945 --> 00:08:02.982 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
but it's the unconscious,
the archaic wiring,

00:08:02.982 --> 00:08:06.486 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
the primal existential
fears that are actually

00:08:06.486 --> 00:08:08.154 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:65%
driving the whole machine.

00:08:13.393 --> 00:08:16.629 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:75%
Endless patterns of grasping
towards pleasure and avoidance

00:08:16.629 --> 00:08:21.101 align:middle line:79% position:38% size:68%
of pain are sublimated into
pathological behaviors.

00:08:21.835 --> 00:08:26.673 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:45%
Our work, 
our relationships,

00:08:28.241 --> 00:08:31.978 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:45%
our beliefs, 
our very thoughts,

00:08:31.978 --> 00:08:33.546 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:70%
and our whole way of living.

00:08:37.350 --> 00:08:41.654 align:start line:79% position:44% size:78%
Like cattle, most humans live
and die in passive subjugation,

00:08:43.556 --> 00:08:45.492 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:48%
feeding their lives
to the matrix.

00:09:08.348 --> 00:09:12.185 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:53%
We live lives locked
into narrow patterns.

00:09:12.185 --> 00:09:15.355 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:53%
Lives often filled
with great suffering.

00:09:15.355 --> 00:09:18.591 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:75%
And it never occurs to us that
we can actually become free.

00:09:26.232 --> 00:09:29.169 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
It is possible to let
go of the life that has

00:09:29.169 --> 00:09:31.070 align:middle line:85% position:45% size:73%
been inherited from the past.

00:09:34.073 --> 00:09:36.709 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
To live the one that is
waiting to come forth

00:09:36.709 --> 00:09:38.445 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:61%
through the inner world.

00:10:08.475 --> 00:10:12.312 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:81%
We were all born into this world
with biological conditioned

00:10:12.312 --> 00:10:16.182 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
structures, but
without self-awareness.

00:10:20.687 --> 00:10:23.556 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
Often when you look into
a young child's eyes,

00:10:23.556 --> 00:10:27.527 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
there's no trace of self,
only luminous emptiness.

00:10:31.831 --> 00:10:36.035 align:start line:79% position:40% size:75%
The person one grows into is a
mask worn over consciousness.

00:10:40.240 --> 00:10:44.010 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
Shakespeare said, 
"all the world's a stage

00:10:44.010 --> 00:10:47.647 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:65%
and all the men and women,
merely players."

00:10:54.187 --> 00:10:57.357 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:65%
In an awakened individual,
consciousness

00:10:57.357 --> 00:11:00.760 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
shines through the personality,
through the mask.

00:11:04.464 --> 00:11:06.666 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:48%
When you are awake,
you don't become

00:11:06.666 --> 00:11:08.668 align:middle line:85% position:44% size:78%
identified with your character.

00:11:09.202 --> 00:11:12.272 align:start line:79% position:44% size:78%
You don't believe that you are
the masks that you are wearing.

00:11:17.176 --> 00:11:19.312 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:48%
But nor do you give
up playing a role.

00:11:42.468 --> 00:11:47.173 align:middle line:79% position:38% size:68%
When we are identified with
our character, our persona,

00:11:47.173 --> 00:11:50.410 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:53%
this is Maya, the
illusion of the self.

00:11:54.314 --> 00:11:57.951 align:middle line:79% position:38% size:68%
Samadhi is awakening from
the dream of your character

00:11:57.951 --> 00:11:59.285 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:50%
in the play of life.

00:12:13.032 --> 00:12:17.537 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
2,400 years after Plato
wrote the "Republic,"

00:12:17.537 --> 00:12:21.140 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
humanity is still making
its way out of Plato's cave.

00:12:25.645 --> 00:12:29.082 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
In fact, we may be more
transfixed by illusions

00:12:29.082 --> 00:12:30.149 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:25%
than ever.

00:12:36.723 --> 00:12:39.058 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:45%
Plato had Socrates
describe a group

00:12:39.058 --> 00:12:42.829 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
of people who lived chained
in a cave all of their lives

00:12:42.829 --> 00:12:44.197 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:50%
facing a blank wall.

00:12:46.399 --> 00:12:49.335 align:middle line:79% position:36% size:73%
All they could see were
shadows projected on the wall

00:12:49.335 --> 00:12:51.704 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
by the things passing
in front of a fire which

00:12:51.704 --> 00:12:53.006 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:41%
was behind them.

00:12:53.773 --> 00:12:55.508 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:48%
This puppet show
became their world.

00:13:00.179 --> 00:13:03.383 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
According to Socrates, 
the shadows

00:13:03.383 --> 00:13:05.418 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:50%
were as close as the
prisoners would ever

00:13:05.418 --> 00:13:07.120 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:56%
get to seeing reality.

00:13:11.190 --> 00:13:14.627 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
Even after being told
about the outside world,

00:13:14.627 --> 00:13:18.197 align:start line:79% position:40% size:75%
they continued to believe that
the shadows were all that is.

00:13:19.499 --> 00:13:22.669 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
Even if they suspected
there was something more,

00:13:22.669 --> 00:13:25.204 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
they were unwilling to
leave what was familiar.

00:13:35.815 --> 00:13:37.950 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:43%
Humanity today is
like the people

00:13:37.950 --> 00:13:40.420 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
who have only seen the
shadows on the cave wall.

00:13:41.487 --> 00:13:44.123 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
The shadows are analogous
to our thoughts.

00:13:45.058 --> 00:13:48.294 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
The world of thinking is
the only world that we know,

00:13:48.294 --> 00:13:50.096 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:50%
but there is
another world that's

00:13:50.096 --> 00:13:53.966 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:65%
beyond thinking, 
beyond the dualistic mind.

00:13:57.103 --> 00:13:59.238 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:45%
Are you willing
to leave the cave?

00:14:00.073 --> 00:14:02.909 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:56%
To leave all that you
have known to find out

00:14:02.909 --> 00:14:04.644 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:63%
the truth of who you are?

00:14:16.622 --> 00:14:18.591 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:56%
In order 
to experience Samadhi,

00:14:18.591 --> 00:14:21.728 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:81%
it's necessary to turn attention
away from the shadows,

00:14:22.495 --> 00:14:25.331 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
away from the thoughts,
towards the light.

00:14:27.433 --> 00:14:30.069 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:53%
When a person is only
used to darkness,

00:14:30.069 --> 00:14:32.872 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
then they must gradually
become accustomed to the light.

00:14:49.455 --> 00:14:52.625 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:50%
Like acclimatizing
to any new paradigm,

00:14:52.625 --> 00:14:57.597 align:start line:79% position:44% size:78%
it takes time and effort and a
willingness to explore the new,

00:14:57.597 --> 00:14:59.265 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:61%
as well as shed the old.

00:15:16.949 --> 00:15:21.254 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:65%
The mind can be likened to
a trap for consciousness,

00:15:21.254 --> 00:15:22.789 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:61%
a labyrinth or a prison.

00:15:30.530 --> 00:15:34.867 align:middle line:79% position:38% size:68%
It is not that you are in
prison, you are the prison.

00:15:44.844 --> 00:15:46.712 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:65%
The prison is an illusion.

00:15:48.514 --> 00:15:51.617 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:56%
If you are identified
with an illusory self,

00:15:51.617 --> 00:15:52.652 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:50%
then you are asleep.

00:15:54.453 --> 00:15:56.689 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:45%
Once you are aware
of the prison,

00:15:56.689 --> 00:15:59.058 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:50%
if you fight to get
out of the illusion,

00:15:59.058 --> 00:16:01.627 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
then you're treating the
illusion as if it's real,

00:16:02.195 --> 00:16:04.330 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:70%
and you still remain asleep.

00:16:05.298 --> 00:16:07.967 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:53%
Except now, the dream
becomes a nightmare.

00:16:08.868 --> 00:16:12.004 align:middle line:79% position:36% size:73%
You'll be chasing and
running from shadows forever.

00:16:19.745 --> 00:16:23.950 align:middle line:79% position:36% size:73%
Samadhi is awakening from the
dream of the separate self

00:16:23.950 --> 00:16:25.451 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:58%
or the egoic construct.

00:16:26.886 --> 00:16:31.023 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:75%
Samadhi is awakening from
identification with the prison

00:16:31.023 --> 00:16:32.525 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:38%
that I call me.

00:16:38.731 --> 00:16:43.269 align:middle line:79% position:36% size:73%
You can never actually be
free because wherever you go,

00:16:43.269 --> 00:16:45.071 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:53%
your prison is there.

00:16:47.340 --> 00:16:51.944 align:start line:79% position:40% size:75%
Awakening is not about getting
rid of the mind or the matrix.

00:16:51.944 --> 00:16:55.481 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
On the contrary, when you're
not identified with it,

00:16:55.481 --> 00:16:58.517 align:middle line:79% position:38% size:68%
then you can experience the
play of life more fully.

00:16:58.517 --> 00:17:02.255 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:65%
Enjoying the show as it is
without craving or fear.

00:17:03.956 --> 00:17:06.158 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
In the ancient teachings,
this was called

00:17:06.158 --> 00:17:10.696 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
the divine game of Leela,
the game of playing in duality.

00:17:22.074 --> 00:17:24.510 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:48%
Human consciousness
is a continuum.

00:17:25.778 --> 00:17:27.980 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:56%
On one extreme humans 
are identified

00:17:27.980 --> 00:17:30.049 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:58%
with the material self.

00:17:31.384 --> 00:17:35.021 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
On the other extreme is
Samadhi, the cessation of self.

00:17:37.556 --> 00:17:41.827 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:65%
Every step we take on the
continuum towards Samadhi,

00:17:41.827 --> 00:17:43.095 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:56%
brings less suffering.

00:17:46.565 --> 00:17:49.902 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
Less suffering does not
mean life is free from pain.

00:17:53.439 --> 00:17:57.376 align:middle line:79% position:36% size:73%
Samadhi is beyond the
duality of pain and pleasure.

00:17:59.011 --> 00:18:01.647 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
What it means is 
that there is less mind,

00:18:01.647 --> 00:18:05.618 align:middle line:79% position:36% size:73%
less self creating resistance
to whatever unfolds.

00:18:06.719 --> 00:18:09.822 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
And not resistance is
what creates suffering.

00:18:22.068 --> 00:18:24.737 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:43%
