The one who is able to
realize inner peace,

00:33:32.911 --> 00:33:38.283 align:middle line:79% position:36% size:73%
irrespective of circumstance,
has attained true Samadhi.

00:33:39.284 --> 00:33:41.920 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:48%
You drop resistance
not because you

00:33:41.920 --> 00:33:46.558 align:start line:79% position:40% size:75%
condone one thing or another,
but so that your inner freedom

00:33:46.558 --> 00:33:48.793 align:middle line:85% position:44% size:78%
is not contingent on the outer.

00:33:52.264 --> 00:33:56.434 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:81%
It's important to note that
when we accept reality as it is,

00:33:56.434 --> 00:33:58.236 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:56%
it doesn't necessarily
mean that we

00:33:58.236 --> 00:34:00.805 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:45%
stop taking action
in the world or we

00:34:00.805 --> 00:34:03.008 align:middle line:85% position:45% size:73%
become meditating passivists.

00:34:03.975 --> 00:34:06.378 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:53%
Actually, the
opposite can be true.

00:34:07.112 --> 00:34:09.514 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:56%
When we're free to act
without being driven

00:34:09.514 --> 00:34:12.017 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:48%
by unconscious
motives, then it is

00:34:12.017 --> 00:34:14.653 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
possible to act in
alignment with the Tao,

00:34:15.453 --> 00:34:18.556 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:65%
with the full force of our
inner energy behind us.

00:34:24.062 --> 00:34:26.564 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:38%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:34:30.068 --> 00:34:33.238 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
Many will argue that in
order to change the world

00:34:33.238 --> 00:34:36.574 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
and bring about peace,
we need to fight harder

00:34:36.574 --> 00:34:38.610 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:75%
against our perceived enemies.

00:34:40.011 --> 00:34:43.148 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:65%
Fighting for peace is
like shouting for silence.

00:34:44.015 --> 00:34:46.751 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
It just creates more
of what you don't want.

00:34:48.820 --> 00:34:51.289 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
These days, there's a
war against everything.

00:34:51.756 --> 00:34:52.958 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:53%
A war against terror.

00:34:53.992 --> 00:34:55.493 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:56%
A war against disease.

00:34:56.528 --> 00:34:57.796 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:53%
A war against hunger.

00:35:00.565 --> 00:35:03.969 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
Every war is actually 
a war against ourselves.

00:35:13.645 --> 00:35:16.548 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:56%
The fight is part of
a collective delusion.

00:35:17.382 --> 00:35:19.050 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:65%
We say that we want peace,

00:35:19.050 --> 00:35:22.587 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:81%
but we continue to elect leaders
who engage in war.

00:35:23.621 --> 00:35:27.659 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
We lie to ourselves saying that
we are for human rights,

00:35:28.226 --> 00:35:31.096 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
but continue to buy
products made in sweatshops.

00:35:32.197 --> 00:35:35.734 align:middle line:79% position:38% size:68%
We say we want clean air,
but we continue to pollute.

00:35:36.534 --> 00:35:39.270 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:45%
We want science to
cure us of cancer

00:35:39.270 --> 00:35:42.173 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
but won't change our
self-destructive habitual

00:35:42.173 --> 00:35:45.010 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
behaviors that make us
more likely to be sick.

00:35:45.877 --> 00:35:49.714 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
We delude ourselves that we
are promoting a better life.

00:35:50.915 --> 00:35:53.418 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
We don't want to see our
hidden parts that are

00:35:53.418 --> 00:35:55.487 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:75%
condoning suffering and death.

00:35:59.090 --> 00:36:05.063 align:start line:79% position:50% size:81%
The belief that we can win a war
against cancer, hunger, terror,

00:36:05.063 --> 00:36:09.300 align:start line:79% position:50% size:81%
or any enemy that was created by
our own thinking and behavior,

00:36:09.834 --> 00:36:13.238 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
actually lets us continue
to delude ourselves.

00:36:13.238 --> 00:36:17.142 align:start line:79% position:50% size:81%
That we don't have to change the
way we operate on this planet.

00:36:18.810 --> 00:36:21.546 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
The inner world is where
the revolution must first

00:36:21.546 --> 00:36:22.814 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:28%
take place.

00:36:25.250 --> 00:36:29.354 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:75%
Only when we can directly feel
the spiral of life within,

00:36:29.354 --> 00:36:32.490 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
will the outer world come
into alignment with the Tao.

00:36:34.392 --> 00:36:39.230 align:start line:79% position:50% size:81%
Until then, anything we do will
add to the chaos already created

00:36:39.230 --> 00:36:40.165 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:31%
by the mind.

00:36:42.067 --> 00:36:45.437 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
War and peace arise together
in an endless dance.

00:36:46.738 --> 00:36:48.239 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:58%
They are one continuum.

00:36:49.541 --> 00:36:51.776 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:53%
One half cannot exist
without the other.

00:36:53.078 --> 00:36:55.547 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:50%
Just as light cannot
exist without dark.

00:36:55.814 --> 00:36:57.749 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:48%
And up cannot
exist without down.

00:36:59.184 --> 00:37:01.920 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
The world seems to want
light without darkness.

00:37:02.454 --> 00:37:04.089 align:middle line:85% position:46% size:68%
Fullness without emptiness.

00:37:05.824 --> 00:37:07.959 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:65%
Happiness without sadness.

00:37:25.510 --> 00:37:28.012 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:38%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:37:32.484 --> 00:37:35.653 align:middle line:79% position:36% size:73%
The more the mind gets
involved, the more fragmented

00:37:35.653 --> 00:37:36.888 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:45%
the world becomes.

00:37:38.456 --> 00:37:40.959 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
Every solution that
comes from the egoic mind

00:37:40.959 --> 00:37:44.162 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
is driven by the idea
that there is a problem,

00:37:44.696 --> 00:37:47.232 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
and the solution becomes 
an even greater problem

00:37:47.232 --> 00:37:49.300 align:middle line:79% position:46% size:41%
than what it was
trying to solve.

00:37:53.104 --> 00:37:55.573 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:65%
What you resist, persists.

00:38:07.552 --> 00:38:11.189 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
Human ingenuity creates
new antibiotics

00:38:11.189 --> 00:38:14.325 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:50%
only to find nature
getting more cunning

00:38:14.325 --> 00:38:16.127 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:63%
as bacteria get stronger.

00:38:17.028 --> 00:38:20.532 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
Despite our best efforts
in the ongoing fight,

00:38:20.532 --> 00:38:23.535 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
the prevalence of cancer
is actually increasing.

00:38:24.736 --> 00:38:28.306 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
The number of hungry people
in the world steadily grows.

00:38:30.008 --> 00:38:34.579 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
The number of terrorist attacks
worldwide continues to rise.

00:38:41.252 --> 00:38:42.854 align:middle line:85% position:44% size:78%
What's wrong with our approach?

00:38:45.423 --> 00:38:48.726 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:75%
Like the sorcerer's apprentice
from Goethe's poem,

00:38:48.726 --> 00:38:51.095 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:45%
we have taken hold
of a great power,

00:38:51.095 --> 00:38:53.565 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:56%
but we do not have the
wisdom to wield it.

00:38:59.103 --> 00:39:01.706 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
The problem is that we do
not understand the tool

00:39:01.706 --> 00:39:02.707 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:45%
that we are using.

00:39:03.474 --> 00:39:05.710 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:53%
We do not understand 
the human mind

00:39:05.710 --> 00:39:08.079 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:81%
and its proper role and purpose.

00:39:17.288 --> 00:39:18.256 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:38%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:39:18.256 --> 00:39:21.593 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
The crisis is born of the
limited conditioned way

00:39:21.593 --> 00:39:25.630 align:middle line:79% position:36% size:73%
in which we think, the way
we feel, and experience life.

00:39:35.206 --> 00:39:38.576 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
Our rationalism has
robbed us of our ability

00:39:38.576 --> 00:39:41.746 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:53%
to recognize and
experience the wisdom

00:39:41.746 --> 00:39:43.581 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:63%
of many ancient cultures.

00:39:48.286 --> 00:39:51.522 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
Our egoic thinking has
robbed us of the ability

00:39:51.522 --> 00:39:55.793 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
to feel the depth and
profound sacredness of life.

00:39:56.594 --> 00:39:58.363 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:58%
The numinosity of life.

00:39:58.896 --> 00:40:01.599 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
And to realize entirely
different levels

00:40:01.599 --> 00:40:05.803 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
of consciousness, which are
now almost lost to humanity.

00:40:11.509 --> 00:40:14.112 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:48%
In the ancient
Egyptian tradition,

00:40:14.112 --> 00:40:17.915 align:middle line:79% position:38% size:68%
Nedirs were archetypal
forms whose characteristics

00:40:17.915 --> 00:40:20.418 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:50%
could be embodied by
those who purified

00:40:20.418 --> 00:40:23.955 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
their physical and spiritual
bodies in such a way

00:40:23.955 --> 00:40:27.292 align:middle line:79% position:38% size:68%
that they were fit to house
higher consciousnesses.

00:40:30.561 --> 00:40:33.698 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:56%
The original Nedir, or
the divine principle

00:40:33.698 --> 00:40:37.835 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
of this wisdom, was known
as Thoth for Tahuti.

00:40:38.803 --> 00:40:43.141 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
Often depicted as a scribe with
the head of a bird, or ibis,

00:40:43.141 --> 00:40:46.611 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
and represented the origin
of all knowledge and wisdom.

00:40:49.380 --> 00:40:52.684 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
Thoth could be described 
as the cosmic principle

00:40:52.684 --> 00:40:54.585 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:58%
of thinking or thought.

00:40:57.021 --> 00:41:02.126 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
Thoth gave us language,
concepts, writing, mathematics,

00:41:02.126 --> 00:41:05.263 align:middle line:79% position:38% size:68%
and all the arts and
manifestations of the mind.

00:41:07.365 --> 00:41:10.134 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
Only those who had gone
through special training

00:41:10.134 --> 00:41:13.237 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
were allowed to access
Thoth's sacred knowledge.

00:41:18.176 --> 00:41:20.511 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:50%
The Book of Thoth is
not a physical book,

00:41:21.179 --> 00:41:24.582 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
but is the wisdom of the
Akashic or etheric realm.

00:41:27.485 --> 00:41:30.822 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
Legend tells that Thoth's
knowledge was deeply

00:41:30.822 --> 00:41:34.092 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
hidden in a secret place
within every human being,

00:41:34.525 --> 00:41:37.228 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:50%
and was protected
by a golden serpent.

00:41:42.633 --> 00:41:46.571 align:middle line:79% position:36% size:73%
The archetypal or perennial
myth of the serpent or dragon

00:41:46.571 --> 00:41:50.975 align:middle line:79% position:36% size:73%
guarding a treasure is one
that permeates many cultures.

00:41:55.413 --> 00:42:01.652 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:75%
And has been called by names
such as Kundalini Shakti, Chi,

00:42:01.652 --> 00:42:04.288 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:75%
Holy Spirit, and inner energy.

00:42:06.357 --> 00:42:10.128 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
The golden serpent is
the egoic construct which

00:42:10.128 --> 00:42:12.263 align:middle line:85% position:44% size:78%
is bound in the inner energies.

00:42:12.897 --> 00:42:15.933 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:56%
And until it's
mastered and overcome,

00:42:15.933 --> 00:42:19.404 align:middle line:79% position:38% size:68%
the soul will never be able
to attain the true wisdom.

00:42:20.204 --> 00:42:22.774 align:middle line:79% position:36% size:73%
It was said that the 
Book of Thoth brought nothing

00:42:22.774 --> 00:42:25.676 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
but suffering to any
individual who read it.

00:42:27.512 --> 00:42:31.582 align:start line:79% position:44% size:78%
Even though they would find the
secrets of the gods themselves

00:42:31.582 --> 00:42:34.051 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:56%
and all that is hidden
within the stars.

00:42:35.987 --> 00:42:38.122 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
What must be understood
is that the book

00:42:38.122 --> 00:42:41.726 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
brought suffering to any
individual who read it

00:42:42.160 --> 00:42:44.829 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:50%
and the ego that
tried to control it.

00:42:46.898 --> 00:42:50.535 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:65%
In the Egyptian tradition,
awakened consciousness

00:42:50.535 --> 00:42:52.937 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:65%
was represented by Osiris.

00:42:53.905 --> 00:42:56.574 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:53%
Without this awakened
consciousness,

00:42:56.574 --> 00:43:00.778 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:75%
any knowledge or understanding
attained by the limited self

00:43:00.778 --> 00:43:04.482 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:81%
would be dangerous,
disconnected from higher wisdom.

00:43:08.486 --> 00:43:11.255 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:81%
The Eye of Horus had to be open.

00:43:16.027 --> 00:43:18.796 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:50%
The esoteric meaning
that we find here

00:43:18.796 --> 00:43:22.166 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:65%
is similar to the more
familiar story of the fall

00:43:22.166 --> 00:43:23.434 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:56%
in the Garden of Eden.

00:43:24.435 --> 00:43:27.405 align:middle line:79% position:38% size:68%
The Book of Thoth parallels
the tree of knowledge,

00:43:27.405 --> 00:43:30.675 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
of good and evil, 
whose fruits Adam and Eve

00:43:30.675 --> 00:43:31.976 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:50%
were tempted to eat.

00:43:41.719 --> 00:43:45.389 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:81%
Humanity, of course, has already
eaten the forbidden fruit.

00:43:46.557 --> 00:43:48.559 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:45%
Already opened
the Book of Thoth.

00:43:49.427 --> 00:43:51.329 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:45%
And has been cast
out of the garden.

00:43:55.766 --> 00:44:00.104 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
The serpent is a metaphor
for the primordial spiral

00:44:00.104 --> 00:44:03.474 align:middle line:79% position:38% size:68%
that extends from the
microcosm to the macrocosm.

00:44:06.811 --> 00:44:10.147 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:45%
Today, the serpent
is living as you.

00:44:11.749 --> 00:44:17.121 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:75%
It is the egoic mind expressed
as the manifested world.

00:44:19.023 --> 00:44:23.027 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
We have never before had
access to so much knowledge.

00:44:23.794 --> 00:44:26.597 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:50%
We've gone deep into
the material world,

00:44:26.597 --> 00:44:29.200 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
even finding the
so-called God Particle.

00:44:30.167 --> 00:44:33.437 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
But we've never been
more  limited, more ignorant

00:44:33.437 --> 00:44:36.974 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:75%
of who we are and how to live.

00:44:36.974 --> 00:44:39.610 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
And we do not understand 
the mechanism

00:44:39.610 --> 00:44:41.812 align:middle line:85% position:45% size:73%
by which we create suffering.

00:45:07.538 --> 00:45:10.041 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:38%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:45:28.593 --> 00:45:31.762 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
Our thinking has created
the world as it is now.

00:45:32.430 --> 00:45:35.032 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
Whenever we label
something as good or bad

00:45:35.032 --> 00:45:38.636 align:middle line:79% position:36% size:73%
or create a preference in our
mind, it's due to the coming

00:45:38.636 --> 00:45:42.373 align:middle line:79% position:36% size:73%
into being of the egoic
structures or self interests.

00:45:44.308 --> 00:45:48.779 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
The solution is not to fight
for peace or conquer nature,

00:45:49.447 --> 00:45:51.649 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:48%
but to simply
recognize the truth

00:45:53.884 --> 00:45:56.887 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
that the very existence
of the ego structure

00:45:56.887 --> 00:46:01.025 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
creates duality, a split
between self and other.

00:46:02.059 --> 00:46:03.127 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:38%
Mine and yours.

00:46:03.961 --> 00:46:05.129 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:38%
Man and nature.

00:46:06.464 --> 00:46:07.832 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:41%
Inner and outer.

00:46:10.968 --> 00:46:13.204 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:50%
The ego is violence.

00:46:13.871 --> 00:46:18.042 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
It requires a barrier, 
a boundary from the other

00:46:18.042 --> 00:46:19.110 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:38%
in order to be.

00:46:20.378 --> 00:46:23.681 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
Without the ego, there is
no war against anything.

00:46:24.382 --> 00:46:25.650 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:48%
There is no hubris.

00:46:26.183 --> 00:46:29.420 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
There is no overreaching
nature to create profit.

00:46:31.222 --> 00:46:33.891 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:48%
These external
crises in our world

00:46:33.891 --> 00:46:36.327 align:middle line:85% position:44% size:78%
reflect a serious inner crisis.

00:46:38.262 --> 00:46:39.964 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:63%
We don't know who we are.

00:46:41.265 --> 00:46:45.102 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
We are completely identified
with our egoic identities,

00:46:45.870 --> 00:46:50.241 align:middle line:79% position:36% size:73%
consumed by fears, and are
cut off from our true nature.

00:46:52.843 --> 00:46:57.381 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
Races, religions, countries,
political affiliations,

00:46:58.049 --> 00:47:01.152 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
and any group that we
belong to all reinforce

00:47:01.152 --> 00:47:02.753 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:53%
our egoic identities.

00:47:04.855 --> 00:47:08.325 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:65%
Almost every group that
exists on the planet today

00:47:08.325 --> 00:47:11.595 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:75%
wants to claim its perspective
as true and correct,

00:47:12.396 --> 00:47:14.498 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:81%
as we do on an individual level.

00:47:15.866 --> 00:47:18.102 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:43%
By claiming the
truth as its own,

00:47:18.102 --> 00:47:21.739 align:middle line:79% position:36% size:73%
the group perpetuates its
own existence in the same way

00:47:21.739 --> 00:47:25.710 align:start line:79% position:36% size:73%
that an ego or self structure
defines itself against other.

00:47:30.081 --> 00:47:33.117 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:48%
Now more than ever,
different realities

00:47:33.117 --> 00:47:36.654 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
and polarized belief systems
are coexisting on Earth.

00:47:37.722 --> 00:47:39.790 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:45%
It is possible for
different people

00:47:39.790 --> 00:47:42.259 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
to experience completely
different thoughts

00:47:42.259 --> 00:47:46.964 align:start line:79% position:40% size:75%
and emotional reactions to the
very same external phenomena.

00:47:48.799 --> 00:47:54.038 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
In the same way, samsara and
nirvana, or heaven and hell,

00:47:54.038 --> 00:47:59.176 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:75%
are two different dimensions
occupying the very same world.

00:48:00.344 --> 00:48:03.681 align:middle line:10% position:43% size:65%
An event that may appear
apocalyptic to one person,

00:48:05.750 --> 00:48:08.085 align:middle line:10% position:45% size:50%
could be seen as a
blessing to another.

00:48:08.085 --> 00:48:10.054 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:35%
[CARS HONKING]

00:48:12.056 --> 00:48:14.258 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:48%
So what is becoming
obvious is that

00:48:14.258 --> 00:48:16.560 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:48%
your external
circumstances don't

00:48:16.560 --> 00:48:19.730 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
have to affect your inner
world in any particular way.

00:48:22.733 --> 00:48:27.238 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:75%
To realize Samadhi is to
become a self-propelled wheel.

00:48:28.205 --> 00:48:32.309 align:middle line:79% position:38% size:68%
To become autonomous, 
a universe unto one's self.

00:48:36.614 --> 00:48:39.383 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
Your experience of life
is not contingent

00:48:39.383 --> 00:48:40.818 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:56%
on changing phenomena.

00:48:44.989 --> 00:48:48.025 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:65%
An analogy can be
made with metatron's cube.

00:48:50.694 --> 00:48:54.832 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:81%
Metatron is mentioned in various
ancient Christian, Islamic,

00:48:54.832 --> 00:48:58.135 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
and Jewish texts, and
is archetypally related

00:48:58.135 --> 00:49:00.271 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:38%
to the Egyptian
Nedir, Thoth,

00:49:00.271 --> 00:49:03.874 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:75%
as well as Hermes Trismegistus
of Greece.

00:49:05.342 --> 00:49:09.580 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:81%
Metatron is intimately connected
with the tetragrammaton.

00:49:10.614 --> 00:49:14.451 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:75%
The tetragrammaton is the
fundamental geometric pattern,

00:49:14.919 --> 00:49:17.721 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:50%
the template or
primordial emanation

00:49:17.721 --> 00:49:20.591 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:53%
of physical reality,
which has been called

00:49:20.591 --> 00:49:22.893 align:middle line:85% position:45% size:73%
the word of God or the logos.

00:49:26.130 --> 00:49:29.466 align:start line:79% position:40% size:75%
Here, we see a two-dimensional
representation of the figure,

00:49:30.334 --> 00:49:33.938 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
but if you look a certain
way, you see a 3-D cube.

00:49:35.739 --> 00:49:39.944 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:75%
When you see the cube, nothing
has changed in the figure,

00:49:39.944 --> 00:49:43.447 align:middle line:79% position:36% size:73%
but your mind has added a
new dimension to your seeing.

00:49:46.083 --> 00:49:49.086 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:45%
Dimensionality, or
one's perspective,

00:49:49.086 --> 00:49:52.456 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:75%
is simply a matter of becoming
habituated to a new way

00:49:52.456 --> 00:49:53.991 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:61%
of perceiving the world.

00:49:56.527 --> 00:50:00.497 align:middle line:79% position:38% size:68%
Upon realizing Samadhi, we
become free of perspective.

00:50:00.965 --> 00:50:04.435 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
We're free to create new
perspectives because there's

00:50:04.435 --> 00:50:08.639 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
no self invested in or attached
to a particular viewpoint.

00:50:17.314 --> 00:50:20.084 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:45%
The greatest minds
in human history

00:50:20.084 --> 00:50:22.519 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:50%
have often pointed
to levels of thought

00:50:22.519 --> 00:50:24.755 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:45%
beyond the limited
self structure.

00:50:26.056 --> 00:50:29.827 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
Einstein said the true
measure of a human being

00:50:29.827 --> 00:50:34.265 align:start line:79% position:40% size:75%
is determined primarily by the
measure and sense in which he

00:50:34.265 --> 00:50:36.901 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
has attained liberation
from the self.

00:50:41.105 --> 00:50:44.808 align:start line:79% position:36% size:73%
So it's not that thinking and
existence of the self is bad.

00:50:45.376 --> 00:50:48.579 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
Thinking is a wonderful
tool when the mind is

00:50:48.579 --> 00:50:50.381 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:61%
in service to the heart.

00:50:53.751 --> 00:50:57.721 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:75%
In Vedanta, it is said that
the mind makes a good servant,

00:50:57.721 --> 00:50:59.056 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:45%
but a poor master.

00:51:06.597 --> 00:51:09.333 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:48%
The ego perpetually
filters reality

00:51:09.333 --> 00:51:10.901 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:70%
through language and labels,

00:51:10.901 --> 00:51:13.637 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:65%
and is constantly judging,

00:51:13.637 --> 00:51:16.340 align:middle line:10% position:43% size:48%
preferring one
thing over another.

00:51:17.875 --> 00:51:21.345 align:middle line:10% position:41% size:58%
When the mind and
senses are your master,

00:51:21.345 --> 00:51:24.782 align:middle line:10% position:43% size:65%
they will create endless
suffering, endless craving

00:51:24.782 --> 00:51:28.686 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
and aversion, locking us
into the matrix of thinking.

00:51:32.723 --> 00:51:34.992 align:middle line:10% position:43% size:48%
If you want 
to realize Samadhi,

00:51:34.992 --> 00:51:38.162 align:middle line:10% position:43% size:65%
do not judge your thoughts
as good or bad,

00:51:38.996 --> 00:51:42.132 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
but find out who you are
prior to thought,

00:51:42.132 --> 00:51:44.468 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:50%
prior to the senses.

00:51:45.970 --> 00:51:47.838 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:70%
When all labels are dropped,

00:51:49.039 --> 00:51:51.842 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:65%
then it is possible to see
things as they are.

00:51:57.581 --> 00:52:00.918 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
The moment a child
is told what a bird is,

00:52:00.918 --> 00:52:03.420 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:45%
if they believe
what they're told,

00:52:05.122 --> 00:52:07.057 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:43%
then they never
see a bird again.

00:52:08.692 --> 00:52:10.561 align:middle line:85% position:45% size:73%
They only see their thoughts.

00:52:11.161 --> 00:52:14.498 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:41%
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

00:52:18.502 --> 00:52:20.971 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:38%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:52:52.269 --> 00:52:56.140 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
Most people think that they
are free, conscious, and awake,

00:52:57.741 --> 00:53:01.745 align:middle line:79% position:36% size:73%
but if you believe you are
already awake, then why would

00:53:01.745 --> 00:53:05.015 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:50%
you do the difficult
work to attain what

00:53:05.015 --> 00:53:07.017 align:middle line:85% position:45% size:73%
you believe you already have?

00:53:08.886 --> 00:53:11.422 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:48%
Before it becomes
possible to awaken,

00:53:11.989 --> 00:53:15.492 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:65%
it is necessary to accept 
that you are asleep

00:53:15.492 --> 00:53:17.561 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:53%
living in the matrix.

00:53:20.597 --> 00:53:24.001 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:65%
Examine your life honestly
without lying to yourself.

00:53:26.203 --> 00:53:28.839 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
Are you able to stop
your robotic, repetitive

00:53:28.839 --> 00:53:30.541 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:38%
life patterns 
if you want to?

00:53:32.309 --> 00:53:35.245 align:middle line:79% position:38% size:68%
Can you stop seeking
pleasure and avoiding pain?

00:53:36.146 --> 00:53:41.785 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
Are you addicted to certain
foods, activities, or pastimes?

00:53:41.785 --> 00:53:45.656 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:45%
Are you constantly
judging, blaming,

00:53:45.656 --> 00:53:47.524 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:81%
criticizing yourself and others?

00:53:49.526 --> 00:53:53.097 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:65%
Does your mind incessantly
seek out stimulus?

00:53:53.664 --> 00:53:57.701 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
Or are you completely fulfilled
just being in silence?

00:53:59.570 --> 00:54:02.539 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
Do you react to how
people think about you?

00:54:02.539 --> 00:54:06.009 align:middle line:79% position:38% size:68%
Are you seeking approval
and positive reinforcement?

00:54:06.643 --> 00:54:10.047 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
Do you somehow sabotage
situations in your life?

00:54:12.216 --> 00:54:15.285 align:middle line:79% position:38% size:68%
Most people will experience
their lives the same way

00:54:15.285 --> 00:54:19.223 align:middle line:79% position:38% size:68%
today as they will tomorrow
and a year from now

00:54:19.223 --> 00:54:20.457 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:56%
and 10 years from now.

00:54:23.026 --> 00:54:25.996 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:63%
When you begin to observe
your robot-like nature,

00:54:26.597 --> 00:54:28.632 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:56%
you become more awake.

00:54:29.633 --> 00:54:32.870 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:65%
You begin to recognize
the depths of the problem.

00:54:35.005 --> 00:54:40.344 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:75%
You are completely and utterly
a sleep, lost in a dream.

00:54:41.879 --> 00:54:46.483 align:start line:79% position:44% size:78%
Like the inhabitants of Plato's
cave, most who hear this truth

00:54:46.483 --> 00:54:49.920 align:middle line:79% position:40% size:75%
will not be willing or capable
of changing their lives

00:54:50.454 --> 00:54:53.257 align:middle line:79% position:38% size:68%
because they are attached
to their familiar patterns.

00:54:55.759 --> 00:54:59.096 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
We go to great lengths
justifying our patterns.

00:54:59.930 --> 00:55:04.001 align:start line:79% position:36% size:73%
Burying our heads in the sand
rather than facing the truth.

00:55:05.869 --> 00:55:08.505 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:50%
We want our saviors,
but we are not

00:55:08.505 --> 00:55:10.908 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:50%
willing to get up on
the cross ourselves.

00:55:12.442 --> 00:55:15.846 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:50%
What are you willing
to pay to be free?

00:55:19.449 --> 00:55:22.719 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
Realize that if you
change your inner world,

00:55:22.719 --> 00:55:25.522 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
you must be prepared to
change the outer life.

00:55:26.490 --> 00:55:29.526 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:53%
Your old structure
and your old identity

00:55:29.526 --> 00:55:33.096 align:middle line:79% position:36% size:73%
must become the dead soil out
of which new growth comes.

00:55:40.103 --> 00:55:43.106 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
The first step to
awakening is to realize

00:55:43.106 --> 00:55:46.910 align:middle line:79% position:36% size:73%
that we are identified with
the matrix of the human mind,

00:55:46.910 --> 00:55:47.911 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:31%
or the mask.

00:55:49.479 --> 00:55:53.116 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:50%
Something within us
must hear this truth

00:55:53.116 --> 00:55:55.118 align:middle line:85% position:44% size:78%
and be roused from its slumber.

00:55:56.453 --> 00:55:59.289 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
There is a part of you,
something timeless,

00:55:59.289 --> 00:56:01.558 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:81%
that has always known the truth.

00:56:18.542 --> 00:56:23.513 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
The matrix of the mind
distracts us, entertains us,

00:56:24.481 --> 00:56:29.186 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:45%
keeps us endlessly
doing, consuming,

00:56:30.187 --> 00:56:34.324 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:56%
grasping in a cycle of
craving and aversion

00:56:34.324 --> 00:56:36.493 align:middle line:85% position:44% size:78%
with constantly changing forms.

00:56:37.794 --> 00:56:41.331 align:middle line:79% position:36% size:73%
Keeping us from the flowering
of our consciousness,

00:56:41.331 --> 00:56:44.635 align:middle line:79% position:38% size:68%
our evolutionary birthright
which is Samadhi.

00:56:47.237 --> 00:56:51.074 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:70%
Pathological thinking is
what passes for normal life.

00:56:58.548 --> 00:57:01.551 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:50%
Your divine essence
has become enslaved,

00:57:02.185 --> 00:57:05.522 align:middle line:79% position:41% size:58%
identified with the
limited self structure.

00:57:06.590 --> 00:57:09.393 align:middle line:79% position:42% size:53%
The great wisdom, the
truth of who you are,

00:57:09.960 --> 00:57:11.995 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:45%
is buried deep
within your being.

00:57:20.203 --> 00:57:25.676 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:65%
J. Krishnamurti said it is
no measure of one's health

00:57:25.676 --> 00:57:29.446 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:61%
to be well adjusted to a
profoundly sick society.

00:57:38.989 --> 00:57:42.659 align:middle line:79% position:43% size:65%
Identification with the
egoic mind is the sickness

00:57:44.594 --> 00:57:47.998 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:61%
and Samadhi is the cure.

00:57:47.998 --> 00:57:49.999 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:38%
[MUSIC PLAYING]